title: Find Peak Element
description: A peak element is an element that is strictly greater than its neighbors. Given a 0-indexed integer array nums, find a peak element, and return its index. If the array contains multiple peaks, return the index to any of the peaks. You may imagine that nums[-1] = nums[n] = -infinity. You must write an algorithm that runs in O(log n) time.
output_format: An integer representing the index of a peak element.
